  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to essential WASH services for IDPs in A&#x2019;zaz District, Aleppo Governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SI&#x2019;s presence in Aleppo Governorate&#x2019;s territory since 2012 allowed the organization to build a robust knowledge and credibility within the local communities to be able to analyze and respond to the evolution of needs in the area. Following a KAP survey done in December 2017 and SI long term presence and assistance to the population of the area, SI&#x2019;s knowledge of the context and the needs taking into account the constraints of a critical moment where humanitarian needs are high in the region but access difficulties make humanitarian interventions more and more challenging to operate, SI is proposing to provide target IDPs with adequate access to a comprehensive package of WASH activities by ensuring the continuation of its lifesaving services in 6 IDP settlements in A&#x2019;zaz district (Karaj Sijjo, Ehtemlat, Dabiq, Yazibagh Al Jabal, Al Mokawama and Al Resala) and addressing a total population of 39,610 individuals.
While SI is currently securing other funding sources to provide the target IDP populations with durable water supply solutions, it is imperative to continue emergency support to IDPs with WASH essential services. SI&#x2019;s package will include: supply of safe water to target camps in adequate quantity through water trucking water quality insurance through treatment at water truck and monitoring at water point, truck and household level to ensure water quality, according to standards maintenance of gender appropriate distribution points for timely and protective water collection provision of waste removal and sanitation facilities cleaning and maintenance services, along with HP awareness for the entire population of the target camps. In parallel to this project, SI is under advanced negotiations with another donor to secure funding for contingency and emergency response related to Idleb military campaign.</narrative>
  </description>
